    "They are each parameterised by the sl(2, R)-spin j, which is real and positive for the discrete representations, whilst j = 1 2 + is for real s ≥ 0 for the continuous representations.",
    "It is the continuous representations that are of interest for the current work and we denote these by C j λ, where λ is the fractional part of the J 3 0 eigenvalue.",
    "These sl(2, R) representations should of course sit in a larger multiplet for psu(1, 1|2).",
    "However, in the minimal tension limit of k = 1, there is a shortening of the spectrum such that the only unitary representations of psu(1, 1|2) that are allowed for the affine Lie superalgebra psu(1, 1|2) 1 take the form [3] (C1 2 λ, 2) (C 1 λ+ 1 2, 1) (C 0 λ+ 1 2, 1) (3.1)where we denote n-dimensional representations of su(2) by n and the supercharges S αA± 0 move between the representations.",
    "Since the top sl(2, R) representation has j = 1 2, we refer to this multiplet as the \"j = 1 2 solution\", which lies at the bottom of the continuum of states."
